P(A\cap B)=P(A)P(B)
A\subseteq B
A\cap B=A
A
B
E_1 = \{HHH, THH, HTH, HHT\}
E_2 = \{THH, HTH, HHT\}
E_3 = \{HHH, TTT\}
p E_1 = \frac{4}{8}
p E_2 = \frac{3}{8}
p E_3 = \frac{2}{8}
E_1 \cap E_2 = E_2
E_1 \cap E_3 = \{ HHH \}
E_2 \cap E_3 = \emptyset
p (E_1 \cap E_2) = \frac{3}{8}
p (E_1 \cap E_3) = \frac{1}{8}
p (E_2 \cap E_3) = 0
p (E_i \cap E_j) = p E_i p E_j
